Pre-Game Insights: Liberia were denied a dream start to the 2026 World Cup qualifiers as they suffered a 1-0 defeat at the hand of Malawi.
Teenage striker Chifundo Mphasi came off the bench to grab the headlines as he scored the winning goal in the 78th minute to hand the Flames all three points against Malawi.

Liberia have now lost five games on the bounce and are without a win in their last eight across all competitions, losing six and claiming two draws since a 2-1 victory over Senegal in the Africa Nations Championship in July 2022.
Equatorial Guinea could not have hoped for a better start to their hunt for a first World Cup appearance as they picked up a 1-0 victory over Namibia.
Former Middlesbrough and Birmingham City man Emilio Nsue delivered the goods once again as he found the back of the net in the 64th minute to hand the hosts all three points against Namibia.
Equatorial Guinea have won one of their five competitive games in 2023, with a 1-1 draw against Libya being the exception.
